<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1185" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1185">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.94/1b.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Japanese
                                    Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I desire to inform you
                            that after your call on Friday the 26th instant the Department sent
                            telegraphic instructions to the Consul of the United States at Chihuahua
                            to use his good offices in behalf of Japanese subjects as he had done in
                            the case of other aliens.</p>
                        <p>The Department has also taken up with the Department of Labor the
                            question of affording temporary refuge at El Paso to Japanese subjects
                            in case they should be obliged to leave Chihuahua.</p>
                        <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>